        "subtitle": "Predict Used Car Prices from Easy-to-Understand Vehicle Features",
        "description": "#  Used Car Price Estimation Dataset\n\n##  Overview\nThis dataset contains **10,000 realistic entries** of used cars with various features such as mileage, engine size, number of previous owners, fuel type, and more. It is designed for **regression tasks** where the goal is to **predict the resale price** of a car in USD.\n\nIt\u2019s perfect for:\n- Practicing regression models\n- Exploring feature importance\n- Building interactive dashboards\n- Training ML models for real-world pricing prediction\n\n\n##  Use Cases\n- **Regression**: Predict `price_usd` using the other features.\n- **Feature Engineering**: Create new features like car age, fuel economy score, etc.\n- **Data Visualization**: Analyze how different factors like engine size or brand impact price.\n- **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)**: Great for beginners to learn cleaning and insights.\n\n\n##  Format\n- **File type**: CSV  \n- **Rows**: 10,000  \n- **File name**: `used_car_price_dataset_extended.csv`\n\n\n##  License & Credits\nThis dataset is **synthetically generated** and does not represent any real-world individual's data. Free to use for learning, teaching, and experimentation.\n\n\n=== About this file ===\n\nAbout this file\nFilename\nDescription\nRows\nFormat\nused_car_price_dataset_extended.csv\nFull dataset with 10,000 used car records\n10,000\nCSV\n\n\n=== Columns & descriptions ===\n\nmake_year: Year the car was manufactured (between 1995 and 2023).\nmileage_kmpl: Mileage of the car in kilometers per liter (kmpl).\nengine_cc: Engine capacity in cubic centimeters (e.g., 1200 cc, 2000 cc).\nfuel_type: Type of fuel used: Petrol, Diesel, or Electric.\nowner_count: Number of previous owners (1 to 5).\nprice_usd: arget variable \u2013 resale price of the car in US dollars (USD).\nbrand: Car brand name\ntransmission: Type of transmission: Manual or Automatic.\ncolor: Exterior color of the car.\nservice_history: Maintenance history: Full, Partial, or None.\naccidents_reported: Number of accidents reported for the vehicle (typically 0\u20135).\ninsurance_valid: Indicates whether insurance is currently valid: Yes or No.\n",
